Analiza danych

Rozkad wagi cakowitej naszych abalone (uchowcw, dziwnych zwierztek).

## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

Sprawdzenie oddzielnie, mao kolumn, w ramach szukania ciekawych zalenoci. Szukanie do skutku.

#zalenoci midzy zmiennymi
ggplot(abalone, aes(length, whole_weight))+
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method="lm", color="red", se=FALSE) +
  labs(title = "Zaleno dugoci i wagi")

ggplot(abalone, aes(height, whole_weight))+
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method="lm", color="red", se=FALSE) +
  labs(title = "Zaleno wysokoci i wagi")

ggplot(abalone, aes(diameter, whole_weight))+
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method="lm", color="red", se=FALSE) +
  labs(title = "Zaleno ... i wagi")

ggplot(abalone, aes(viscera_weight, whole_weight))+
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method="lm", color="red", se=FALSE) +
  labs(title = "Zaleno ... i wagi")

ggplot(abalone, aes(shucked_weight, whole_weight))+
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method="lm", color="red", se=FALSE) +
  labs(title = "Zaleno ... i wagi")

ggplot(abalone, aes(rings, whole_weight))+
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method="lm", color="red", se=FALSE) +
  labs(title = "Zaleno ... i wagi")

Okazuje si, e waga koreluje ze wszytkimi kolumnami w podobny sposb.
